<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take a flight • take flight</xh5><p> <i>take a flight—</i>make a journey by air: She had to drive home alone, while he <u>took a shuttle flight</u> in the opposite direction. </p><p><i>take flight</i>—(also: take to flight) 1. run away (from danger, etc.): Fear and panic gripped people and many <u>took flight</u> into fields and woods at the air-raid warning. 2. <i>(of birds)</i> rise into the air; start flying <i>(also: take wing):</i> The larger groundfeeding birds seldom <u>take flight</u> except to escape danger.</p> </entry>
